text: Knut Jacobsen (11 November 1885 - after 1973) was a Norwegian banker and politician. Jacobsen was born in Haugesund to merchant Svend Jacobsen and Berta Karine Rossebø. He was elected representative to the Stortinget for the period 1934-1936, for the Conservative Party. ==References== Category:1885 births Category:Year of death missing Category:People from Haugesund Category:Norwegian bankers Category:Conservative Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting
